parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the door hinge can cause the door to sag or fall off, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the door opens while the vehicle is in motion.
symptoms: The door sags or falls off
the door hinge weld breaks
the door does not close properly
the door opens while the vehicle is in motion
the door hinge separates from the frame
the door is loose and difficult to close.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the frame can cause the vehicle to collapse or lose its structural integrity, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The frame collapses
the seat does not hold together
the vehicle rolls over
the door is ejected from the vehicle.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the engine mount can cause the engine to drop, leading to damage to the engine block, exhaust system, and other components, which can result in costly repairs and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The engine mount bolts shear off
the engine drops
the vehicle stalls or shuts off
the exhaust system is damaged
and the radiator fan hits the fan shroud.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling or shutting off can cause accidents, especially if it occurs at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls or shuts off without warning
the vehicle loses power
and the engine may hesitate or sputter before stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Excessive oil consumption or leakage can cause engine damage, leading to costly repairs and potentially causing accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive oil
oil leaks from the engine
and the engine may run rough or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause the engine to run rough, stall, or shut off, leading to accidents and costly repairs.
symptoms: The catalytic converter fails
the engine runs rough
and the vehicle may stall or shut off.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the exhaust system can cause the engine to run rough, stall, or shut off, leading to accidents and costly repairs.
symptoms: The exhaust system leaks
the exhaust manifold cracks
and the engine may run rough or stall.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake rotors can cause the vehicle to vibrate or shake when braking, leading to extended stopping distances, accidents, and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle vibrates or shakes when braking
the brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brakes lock up in damp
wet
or snowy weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake system can cause accidents, injuries, and fatalities due to extended stopping distances, loss of control, and inability to stop the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle is unable to stop
the vehicle pulls to one side when braking
the brakes lock up in damp
wet
or snowy weather.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the manufacturer to properly address recall issues can lead to continued safety risks, financial losses, and frustration for vehicle owners.
symptoms: The manufacturer refuses to honor recall repairs
the dealership fails to complete recall repairs
the vehicle owner is denied reimbursement for prior repairs.
